  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1463",
  "title": "Helper configuration (for distinct)",
  "body": "Hi,\n\nFollowing #1027, #1031 and #1106, I am still a bit unclear about what is the recommended / future-proof way of configuring the helper, for setting the distinct parameter in particular. At the moment, the helper is exposed to me in two places :\n### Custom searchFunction\n\n``` javascript\nvar search = instantsearch({\n [...]\n  searchFunction: search_func\n});\n\nfunction search_func(helper) {  \n  // does not work, distinct is not set in the query\n  // helper.setQueryParameter('distinct', 3).search();\n}\n```\n### Custom widget\n\n``` javascript\nsearch.addWidget({\n  init: function(args) {\n    args.helper.setQueryParameter('distinct', 3);\n  }\n});\n```\n\nI had to resort to using option 2 (custom widget) but as @pixelastic pointed out \n\n> I would rather keep the widgets for everything that is DOM/UI related\n\nCould you please let me know if the custom widget is the way to go as of now for this kind of customizations?\n\nThanks!\n",
